## 1. Prerequisites & System Requirements

> 🔗 **Official Reference:** https://docs.expo.dev/get-started/set-up-your-environment/

### Minimum Requirements

| Requirement | Version | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Node.js | 18.x LTS or 20.x LTS | Avoid odd-numbered versions |
| npm | 9.x+ (bundled with Node) | Or use yarn 3.x / pnpm 8.x |
| Git | 2.x+ | Required for EAS |
| Expo CLI | Latest | `npx expo` or global install |
| EAS CLI | Latest | For builds & submissions |

### For iOS Builds (Required)
- macOS 13 (Ventura) or newer
- Xcode 15 or newer (from Mac App Store)
- Apple Developer Account ($99/year) → https://developer.apple.com/programs/
- iOS 16+ physical device or Simulator

### For Android Builds
- Android Studio (for local testing) → https://developer.android.com/studio
- Google Play Developer Account ($25 one-time) → https://play.google.com/console/
- Java Development Kit (JDK) 17 — bundled with Android Studio

### Cloud Builds (No Mac Needed for iOS)
EAS Build runs on Expo's cloud infrastructure. You can build iOS apps from Windows/Linux using EAS Build without owning a Mac.
> 🔗 https://docs.expo.dev/build/introduction/

