## 4. Create a New Expo Project

> 🔗 **Official Reference:** https://docs.expo.dev/get-started/create-a-project/

### Step 4.1 — Initialize Project

```bash
# Create with latest Expo SDK (recommended)
npx create-expo-app@latest MyAwesomeApp

# Choose a template interactively
npx create-expo-app@latest MyAwesomeApp --template

# With TypeScript (strongly recommended)
npx create-expo-app@latest MyAwesomeApp --template expo-template-blank-typescript

# With Expo Router (file-based navigation)
npx create-expo-app@latest MyAwesomeApp --template expo-template-tabs
```

### Available Official Templates

| Template | Command | Use Case |
|---|---|---|
| Blank | `--template blank` | Minimal starter |
| Blank TypeScript | `--template blank-typescript` | TypeScript starter |
| Tabs (Router) | `--template tabs` | Tab navigation with Expo Router |
| Bare minimum | `--template bare-minimum` | No Expo managed workflow |

> 🔗 All templates: https://docs.expo.dev/more/create-expo/

### Step 4.2 — Navigate to Project and Open

```bash
cd MyAwesomeApp
code .   # Open in VS Code (optional)
```

### Step 4.3 — Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install

# Or with yarn
yarn install
```

