## 5. Project Structure Deep Dive

> 🔗 **Official Reference:** https://docs.expo.dev/develop/project-structure/

### Standard Expo Project Layout

```
MyAwesomeApp/
├── app/                    # Expo Router screens (if using Router)
│   ├── (tabs)/
│   │   ├── index.tsx       # Home screen
│   │   └── explore.tsx     # Explore screen
│   ├── _layout.tsx         # Root layout
│   └── +not-found.tsx      # 404 page
├── assets/                 # Images, fonts, icons
│   ├── fonts/
│   ├── images/
│   └── adaptive-icon.png   # Android adaptive icon
├── components/             # Reusable React components
│   ├── ui/
│   └── ThemedText.tsx
├── constants/              # Colors, sizes, config
│   └── Colors.ts
├── hooks/                  # Custom React hooks
├── scripts/                # Utility scripts
│   └── reset-project.js
├── .expo/                  # Auto-generated Expo cache (git-ignore this)
├── .gitignore
├── app.json                # ⭐ App configuration (name, version, icons)
├── babel.config.js         # Babel transpiler config
├── eas.json                # ⭐ EAS Build profiles
├── expo-env.d.ts           # TypeScript Expo env types
├── package.json            # Dependencies
├── tsconfig.json           # TypeScript config
└── README.md
```

### Key Files Explained

**`app.json`** — Core app metadata. Controls app name, icons, splash screen, permissions.

**`eas.json`** — Build profiles for development, preview, and production builds.

**`babel.config.js`** — Required Babel presets. Do not delete.

**`assets/`** — All static assets. Expo handles optimization automatically.

