## 7. Running the App Locally (Development)

> 🔗 **Official Reference:** https://docs.expo.dev/develop/development-builds/introduction/

### Step 7.1 — Start the Expo Dev Server

```bash
# Start with auto-detected bundler
npx expo start

# Clear cache and start (fixes many issues)
npx expo start --clear

# Tunnel mode (for testing over internet/different network)
npx expo start --tunnel

# Start for specific platform
npx expo start --android
npx expo start --ios
npx expo start --web
```

### Step 7.2 — Metro Bundler Options

After running `npx expo start`, the Metro bundler opens. Use these keyboard shortcuts:

| Key | Action |
|---|---|
| `a` | Open Android emulator |
| `i` | Open iOS simulator |
| `w` | Open in web browser |
| `r` | Reload app |
| `m` | Toggle menu |
| `j` | Open debugger |
| `?` | Show all options |

### Step 7.3 — Enable Fast Refresh

Fast Refresh is **on by default** in Expo. It automatically updates your app when you save files. No configuration needed.
> 🔗 https://docs.expo.dev/workflow/development-mode/

### Step 7.4 — Install Dependencies Correctly

Always use `expo install` instead of `npm install` for Expo-compatible packages:

```bash
# ✅ Correct — installs compatible version
npx expo install expo-camera
npx expo install expo-router react-native-safe-area-context

# ❌ Avoid for Expo packages (may install incompatible version)
npm install expo-camera
```
> 🔗 https://docs.expo.dev/workflow/expo-cli/#install

