## 11. Android Build & Deployment

> 🔗 **Official Reference:** https://docs.expo.dev/build/android/

### Step 11.1 — Set Android Package Name

In `app.json`:
```json
{
  "expo": {
    "android": {
      "package": "com.yourcompany.appname",
      "versionCode": 1
    }
  }
}
```

> ⚠️ **Once published, the package name CANNOT be changed.** Choose carefully.
> Format: `com.companyname.appname` (reverse domain notation)

### Step 11.2 — Generate Android Keystore

EAS can manage your keystore automatically:

```bash
# Let EAS generate and manage your keystore (recommended)
eas credentials

# Select:
# > Android
# > Your app
# > Set up a new keystore

# EAS will generate and securely store your keystore on Expo servers
```

> 🔗 https://docs.expo.dev/app-signing/android-credentials/

**To use your own keystore:**
```bash
# Generate keystore locally
keytool -genkeypair -v \
  -storetype PKCS12 \
  -keystore my-upload-key.keystore \
  -alias my-key-alias \
  -keyalg RSA \
  -keysize 2048 \
  -validity 10000

# Then upload to EAS
eas credentials --platform android
```

### Step 11.3 — Build for Android

```bash
# Build APK for internal testing (preview profile)
eas build --platform android --profile preview

# Build AAB for Play Store (production profile)
eas build --platform android --profile production

# Build both platforms at once
eas build --platform all --profile production
```

After running, EAS will:
1. Ask to generate/use existing keystore
2. Upload your code to Expo build servers
3. Provide a build URL to monitor progress
4. Email you when build completes

**Check build status:**
```bash
eas build:list
```
> 🔗 Monitor at: https://expo.dev/builds

### Step 11.4 — Download & Test APK

```bash
# List recent builds
eas build:list --platform android

# Download latest build (APK)
# Or download via URL shown in build output
```

Install on device:
```bash
# Using ADB (Android Debug Bridge)
adb install path/to/app.apk

# Or simply scan the QR code from Expo dashboard
```

### Step 11.5 — Set Up Google Play Console

1. Go to **https://play.google.com/console/**
2. Create a new app → **Create App**
3. Fill in:
   - App name
   - Default language
   - App or Game type
   - Free or Paid
4. Accept policies → **Create App**
5. Complete the store listing:
   - Short description (80 chars max)
   - Full description (4000 chars max)
   - App icon (512x512 px PNG)
   - Feature graphic (1024x500 px)
   - Screenshots (at least 2 per device type)

### Step 11.6 — Create Google Service Account (for Automated Submission)

> 🔗 https://docs.expo.dev/submit/android/

1. Go to **Google Play Console** → **Setup** → **API access**
2. Link to a Google Cloud Project
3. Create a **Service Account** in Google Cloud Console
4. Grant the service account **Release Manager** role in Play Console
5. Download the JSON key file → save as `google-service-account.json`

> ⚠️ **Security:** Add `google-service-account.json` to `.gitignore` immediately!

### Step 11.7 — Submit to Google Play

**Automated submission via EAS:**
```bash
# Submit the latest successful production build
eas submit --platform android --profile production

# Submit a specific build
eas submit --platform android --id BUILD_ID_FROM_EAS
```

**Manual submission:**
1. Download the `.aab` file from Expo dashboard
2. Go to Play Console → **Production** → **Create new release**
3. Upload the AAB file
4. Add release notes
5. Click **Review release** → **Start rollout to Production**

### Step 11.8 — Android App Signing (Important!)

Google Play App Signing manages your release key. When you first upload:
1. Play Console uses **upload key** (your keystore) to verify identity
2. Google re-signs with a **release key** it manages
3. **Never lose your upload keystore** — it's needed for future updates

> 🔗 https://docs.expo.dev/app-signing/android-credentials/

