## 12. iOS Build & Deployment

> 🔗 **Official Reference:** https://docs.expo.dev/build/ios/

### Step 12.1 — Apple Developer Account Setup

1. Go to **https://developer.apple.com/programs/**
2. Enroll in the **Apple Developer Program** ($99/year)
3. Complete identity verification (may take 24–48 hours)
4. Once approved, access the Apple Developer Portal at **https://developer.apple.com/account/**

### Step 12.2 — Set iOS Bundle Identifier

In `app.json`:
```json
{
  "expo": {
    "ios": {
      "bundleIdentifier": "com.yourcompany.appname",
      "buildNumber": "1",
      "supportsTablet": true
    }
  }
}
```

> ⚠️ **Bundle Identifier CANNOT be changed** once the app is on the App Store. Use reverse domain format.

### Step 12.3 — Configure iOS Credentials

EAS handles all iOS credentials automatically:

```bash
# Let EAS manage credentials (recommended)
eas credentials --platform ios

# EAS will create/manage:
# - Distribution Certificate
# - Provisioning Profile (Ad Hoc / App Store)
# - Push Notification Key (if needed)
```

**What EAS manages for you:**
- **Distribution Certificate** — Proves the app is from you
- **Provisioning Profile** — Links app ID + devices + certificate
- **App Store Connect API Key** — For automated submissions

> 🔗 https://docs.expo.dev/app-signing/ios-credentials/

### Step 12.4 — Register Devices for TestFlight (Ad Hoc Testing)

```bash
# Register test devices
eas device:create

# This provides a URL/QR code testers open on their iPhone
# They install a profile, which registers their UDID
```
> 🔗 https://docs.expo.dev/build/internal-distribution/

### Step 12.5 — Build for iOS Simulator

```bash
# Build for iOS Simulator (no Apple account needed)
eas build --platform ios --profile development

# Or start locally without EAS
npx expo run:ios
```

### Step 12.6 — Build for iOS Device (TestFlight)

```bash
# Build for internal distribution (ad hoc / TestFlight)
eas build --platform ios --profile preview

# Build for App Store submission (production)
eas build --platform ios --profile production
```

The build process will:
1. Prompt to use or generate Apple credentials
2. Ask for Apple ID if credentials need to be created
3. Upload code to Expo's macOS build machines
4. Sign the IPA with correct certificates
5. Notify you when complete

**Monitor build:**
```bash
eas build:list --platform ios
# or visit https://expo.dev/builds
```

### Step 12.7 — Set Up App Store Connect

1. Go to **https://appstoreconnect.apple.com/**
2. Click **My Apps** → **+** → **New App**
3. Fill in:
   - Platform: iOS
   - Name: Your App Name
   - Primary Language
   - Bundle ID: Must match `app.json` exactly
   - SKU: Unique internal identifier (e.g., `MYAPP2024`)
   - User Access: Full Access

### Step 12.8 — Create App Store Connect API Key (Automated Submission)

> 🔗 https://docs.expo.dev/submit/ios/

1. App Store Connect → **Users and Access** → **Integrations** → **App Store Connect API**
2. Click **Generate API Key**
3. Select **Role: App Manager**
4. Download the `.p8` key file
5. Note the **Key ID** and **Issuer ID**

```bash
# Upload API key to EAS credentials
eas credentials --platform ios
# Select "App Store Connect API Key"
```

### Step 12.9 — Submit to App Store

**Automated via EAS:**
```bash
# Submit the latest successful production iOS build
eas submit --platform ios --profile production

# This will:
# 1. Upload the IPA to App Store Connect via Transporter
# 2. Process typically takes 10-30 minutes
# 3. Build appears in TestFlight for testing
```

**Manual via Transporter app (macOS):**
1. Download **Transporter** from Mac App Store
2. Sign in with Apple ID
3. Drag and drop the `.ipa` file
4. Click **Deliver**

### Step 12.10 — TestFlight Testing

1. App Store Connect → **TestFlight** tab
2. Add **Internal Testers** (up to 100, must be in your team)
3. Add **External Testers** (up to 10,000, requires Beta App Review ~24–48hrs)
4. Send invitations via email

### Step 12.11 — Submit for App Store Review

1. App Store Connect → Your App → **App Store** tab
2. Fill in complete metadata:
   - App description
   - Keywords (max 100 chars)
   - Screenshots for all required device sizes
   - Privacy Policy URL
   - App Category
   - Age Rating
   - Pricing
3. Under **Build**, select the TestFlight build you've tested
4. Click **Submit for Review**

**Review Timeline:**
- First submission: 1–3 business days
- Subsequent updates: Usually same day

> 🔗 App Review guidelines: https://developer.apple.com/app-store/review/guidelines/

