## 13. OTA Updates with EAS Update

> 🔗 **Official Reference:** https://docs.expo.dev/eas-update/introduction/

EAS Update lets you push JavaScript/asset updates without going through app store review.

### Step 13.1 — Install expo-updates

```bash
npx expo install expo-updates
```

### Step 13.2 — Configure Updates Channel

In `app.json`:
```json
{
  "expo": {
    "updates": {
      "url": "https://u.expo.dev/YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
      "fallbackToCacheTimeout": 0
    },
    "runtimeVersion": {
      "policy": "appVersion"
    }
  }
}
```

> 🔗 https://docs.expo.dev/eas-update/runtime-versions/

### Step 13.3 — Push an OTA Update

```bash
# Publish update to production channel
eas update --channel production --message "Bug fix: login screen"

# Publish to preview channel for testing
eas update --channel preview --message "Testing new feature"

# Update for specific platform only
eas update --channel production --platform android --message "Android-specific fix"
```

### Step 13.4 — Rollback an Update

```bash
# List recent updates
eas update:list

# Rollback to previous update
eas update:rollback --channel production
```

### When OTA Updates Work vs Don't Work

| Change Type | OTA Update | Requires App Store Build |
|---|---|---|
| JavaScript/TypeScript changes | ✅ Yes | ❌ No |
| Image/asset changes | ✅ Yes | ❌ No |
| Text, styling, logic | ✅ Yes | ❌ No |
| New native module added | ❌ No | ✅ Yes |
| `app.json` changes | ❌ No | ✅ Yes |
| SDK version upgrade | ❌ No | ✅ Yes |

