## 14. Environment Variables & Secrets

> 🔗 **Official Reference:** https://docs.expo.dev/build-reference/variables/

### Step 14.1 — Local Environment Variables

Create `.env` file in project root:

```bash
# .env.local (for development)
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://dev.api.example.com
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_KEY=your_key_here

# .env.production
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.example.com
```

> ⚠️ All client-side variables **must be prefixed** with `EXPO_PUBLIC_`. Variables without this prefix are NOT accessible in the app bundle.

**Access in code:**
```typescript
// In your React Native component
const apiUrl = process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL;
console.log(apiUrl); // https://dev.api.example.com
```

### Step 14.2 — Server-Side / Build Secrets (EAS)

For sensitive values (API keys, signing passwords) that shouldn't be in `.env`:

```bash
# Add a secret to EAS (stored securely, not in code)
eas secret:create --scope project --name MY_API_SECRET --value "super-secret-value"

# List secrets
eas secret:list

# Delete a secret
eas secret:delete MY_API_SECRET
```

Access in `eas.json`:
```json
{
  "build": {
    "production": {
      "env": {
        "SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN": "$SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
> 🔗 https://docs.expo.dev/build-reference/variables/#using-secrets-in-environment-variables

### Step 14.3 — .gitignore Setup

```bash
# Add to .gitignore
.env
.env.local
.env.production
google-service-account.json
*.p8
*.keystore
```

