## 15. CI/CD with GitHub Actions

> 🔗 **Official Reference:** https://docs.expo.dev/build/building-on-ci/

### Step 15.1 — Add Expo Token to GitHub Secrets

1. Generate token: `eas account:token:create --name ci-token`
2. Go to GitHub repo → **Settings** → **Secrets and variables** → **Actions**
3. Click **New repository secret**
4. Name: `EXPO_TOKEN`, Value: (paste your token)

### Step 15.2 — Create GitHub Actions Workflow

Create `.github/workflows/build.yml`:

```yaml
name: EAS Build
on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main
  pull_request:
    branches:
      - main

jobs:
  build:
    name: Build and Deploy
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: Checkout repository
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Setup Node.js
        uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: 20.x
          cache: npm

      - name: Install dependencies
        run: npm ci

      - name: Setup Expo and EAS
        uses: expo/expo-github-action@v8
        with:
          eas-version: latest
          token: ${{ secrets.EXPO_TOKEN }}

      - name: Build on EAS (Production)
        run: eas build --platform all --profile production --non-interactive

      - name: Submit to stores
        run: eas submit --platform all --profile production --non-interactive
```

### Step 15.3 — Separate PR Preview Workflow

```yaml
# .github/workflows/preview.yml
name: Preview Build
on:
  pull_request:
    types: [opened, synchronize]

jobs:
  preview:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: 20.x
          cache: npm
      - run: npm ci
      - uses: expo/expo-github-action@v8
        with:
          eas-version: latest
          token: ${{ secrets.EXPO_TOKEN }}
      - name: Create preview build
        run: eas build --platform android --profile preview --non-interactive
      - name: Publish OTA preview update
        run: eas update --channel preview --message "PR preview" --non-interactive
```

> 🔗 https://docs.expo.dev/eas-update/github-actions/

