## 16. Troubleshooting Common Issues

> 🔗 **Official Reference:** https://docs.expo.dev/debugging/errors/

### Issue 1: Metro Bundler Won't Start

```bash
# Kill all node processes and clear cache
npx expo start --clear

# Nuclear option: reset everything
rm -rf node_modules .expo
npm install
npx expo start --clear
```

### Issue 2: "Unable to resolve module" Error

```bash
# Clear Watchman cache (macOS/Linux)
watchman watch-del-all

# Reset Metro cache
npx expo start --reset-cache
```

### Issue 3: EAS Build Fails — Credential Issues

```bash
# Clear and regenerate credentials
eas credentials --platform android
eas credentials --platform ios

# Check credential status
eas credentials:list
```

### Issue 4: iOS Build — "No provisioning profile found"

```bash
# Sync credentials from Apple Developer Portal
eas credentials --platform ios
# Choose: Update provisioning profile
```

### Issue 5: Android Build — Keystore Issues

```bash
# View current keystore info
eas credentials --platform android

# If keystore is lost, you CANNOT update a published app with the same package name
# Start fresh with a new package name (last resort)
```

### Issue 6: App Rejected by App Store

Common rejection reasons and fixes:

| Rejection Reason | Fix |
|---|---|
| Missing privacy policy URL | Add URL to App Store Connect listing |
| Permissions not explained | Update `NSUsageDescription` in `app.json` |
| Crashes on review device | Test on older iOS devices, fix crash |
| Missing iPad screenshots | Add iPad screenshots if `supportsTablet: true` |
| Login required for review | Add demo account credentials in review notes |

### Issue 7: OTA Update Not Showing

```bash
# Check runtime version compatibility
eas update:list

# Verify channel matches in app.json and eas.json
# production channel build must receive production channel updates
```

### Issue 8: expo-router Navigation Issues

```bash
# Reset Expo Router cache
npx expo start --clear

# Check that all files are in correct /app directory
# Ensure _layout.tsx exists at app root
```

### Useful Debugging Commands

```bash
# Check project configuration
npx expo config

# Check if all packages are compatible with SDK version
npx expo doctor

# Detailed doctor check
npx expo-doctor

# View EAS build logs
eas build:view BUILD_ID

# View EAS update status
eas update:list --branch production
```

