## Complete End-to-End Workflow Summary

```
Step 1: Create Expo account at expo.dev/signup
Step 2: Install Node.js (nvm), Git, EAS CLI
Step 3: npx create-expo-app@latest MyApp
Step 4: Configure app.json (bundle ID, icons, permissions)
Step 5: eas login && eas init (links to expo.dev project)
Step 6: eas build:configure (creates eas.json)
Step 7: Test with npx expo start + Expo Go or Dev Build
Step 8: eas build -p android -e preview  →  test APK
Step 9: eas build -p ios -e preview  →  test via TestFlight
Step 10: eas build -p all -e production  →  production builds
Step 11: eas submit -p android  →  Google Play
Step 12: eas submit -p ios  →  App Store Connect
Step 13: Publish JS updates anytime: eas update --channel production
```

